item.dc:creator: @Nuggetdabest Nuggetdabest
item.description:
@Nuggetdabest wrote:

Hmm…

MyComputer/localdisc/programs/java something like that. and you will see your jdk, It will be like "1.6.0_## “##” Is your JDK so if yours is 17. it will be jdk1.6.0._17 NO Space. Go to your compiler right click it,then click edit. Do what Wales 00 said.

[quote=“wales 00, post:20, topic:317597”]USe;

@echo off COLOR 08 "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_17\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java pause[/quote]

jdk1.6.0_17 as your java. then save it. Then try compiling. if it doesn’t work then idk.
